msgctxt "sn12.70:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.70:0.2"
msgid "7. Mahāvagga"
msgstr "7. The Great Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 70. Susimaparibbājakasutta → susīmasuttaṃ (bj) | susīmo (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.70:0.3"
msgid "70. Susimaparibbājakasutta"
msgstr "70. The Wanderer Susīma"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn12.70:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn12.70:1.3"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā sakkato hoti garukato mānito pūjito apacito "
"lābhī cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the Buddha was honored, respected, revered, venerated, and "
"esteemed. And he received robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and "
"supplies for the sick."

msgctxt "sn12.70:1.4"
msgid ""
"Bhikkhusaṃghopi sakkato hoti garukato mānito pūjito apacito lābhī "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the mendicant Saṅgha was also honored, respected, revered, venerated, "
"and esteemed. And they received robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines "
"and supplies for the sick."

msgctxt "sn12.70:1.5"
msgid ""
"Aññatitthiyā pana paribbājakā asakkatā honti agarukatā amānitā apūjitā "
"anapacitā, na lābhino "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But the wanderers who followed other paths were not honored, respected, "
"esteemed, revered, and venerated. And they didn’t receive robes, alms-food, "
"lodgings, and medicines and supplies for the sick."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.120"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: susimo → susīmo (bj, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn12.70:2.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena susimo paribbājako rājagahe paṭivasati mahatiyā "
"paribbājakaparisāya saddhiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time the wanderer Susīma was residing at Rājagaha together with "
"a large community of wanderers."

msgctxt "sn12.70:2.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho susimassa paribbājakassa parisā susimaṃ paribbājakaṃ etadavocuṃ:"
msgstr "Then his community said to Susīma:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:2.3"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, āvuso susima, samaṇe gotame brahmacariyaṃ cara."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Susīma, please live the spiritual life with the ascetic Gotama."

#. VAR: vāceyyāsi → vācessasi (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn12.70:2.4"
msgid "Tvaṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā amhe vāceyyāsi."
msgstr "Memorize that teaching and have us recite it with you."

msgctxt "sn12.70:2.5"
msgid "Taṃ mayaṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇitvā gihīnaṃ bhāsissāma."
msgstr "When we’ve memorized it we’ll recite it to the laity."

msgctxt "sn12.70:2.6"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ mayampi sakkatā bhavissāma garukatā mānitā pūjitā apacitā lābhino "
"cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānan”ti."
msgstr ""
"In this way we too will be honored, respected, esteemed, revered, and "
"venerated. And we’ll receive robes, alms-food, lodgings, and medicines and "
"supplies for the sick.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:2.7"
msgid ""
"“Evamāvuso”ti kho susimo paribbājako sakāya parisāya paṭissuṇitvā yenāyasmā "
"ānando tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā ānandena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"“Yes, reverends,” replied Susīma. Then he went to Venerable Ānanda, and "
"exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn12.70:2.8"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho susimo paribbājako āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:2.9"
msgid ""
"“icchāmahaṃ, āvuso ānanda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Ānanda, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and "
"training.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando susimaṃ paribbājakaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;"
" upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno "
"kho āyasmā ānando bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Ānanda took Susīma to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and said "
"to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:3.2"
msgid "“ayaṃ, bhante, susimo paribbājako evamāha:"
msgstr "“Sir, this wanderer Susīma says that"

msgctxt "sn12.70:3.3"
msgid ""
"‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso ānanda, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’”ti."
msgstr "he wishes to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:3.4"
msgid "“Tenahānanda, susimaṃ pabbājethā”ti."
msgstr "“Well then, Ānanda, give Susīma the going forth.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:3.5"
msgid ""
"Alattha kho susimo paribbājako bhagavato santike pabbajjaṃ, alattha "
"upasampadaṃ."
msgstr ""
"And the wanderer Susīma received the going forth, the ordination in the "
"Buddha’s presence."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.121"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena sambahulehi bhikkhūhi bhagavato santike aññā byākatā "
"hoti:"
msgstr ""
"Now at that time several mendicants had declared their enlightenment in the "
"Buddha’s presence:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.2"
msgid ""
"“khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyāti "
"pajānāmā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“We understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence.’”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.3"
msgid "Assosi kho āyasmā susimo:"
msgstr "Venerable Susīma heard about this."

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.4"
msgid "“sambahulehi kira bhikkhūhi bhagavato santike aññā byākatā:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.5"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāmā”ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā susimo yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā tehi "
"bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr "He went up to those mendicants, and exchanged greetings with them."

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.7"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā susimo te bhikkhū etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to those mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.8"
msgid "“saccaṃ kirāyasmantehi bhagavato santike aññā byākatā:"
msgstr ""
"“Is it really true that the venerables have declared enlightenment in the "
"Buddha’s presence?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.9"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāmā”ti?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.70:4.10"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti."
msgstr "“Yes, reverend.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: Api pana → api nu (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn12.70:5.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā anekavihitaṃ "
"iddhividhaṃ paccanubhotha—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hotha, bahudhāpi hutvā eko "
"hotha; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ, tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamānā "
"gacchatha, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karotha, seyyathāpi "
"udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchatha, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi "
"pallaṅkena kamatha, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye "
"evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimasatha parimajjatha, yāva "
"brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattethā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But knowing and seeing thus, do you wield the many kinds of psychic power? "
"That is, multiplying yourselves and becoming one again; going unimpeded "
"through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; diving in and "
"out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if it were earth; "
"flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and stroking with "
"the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful. Do you control the body "
"as far as the Brahmā realm?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:5.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:6.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā dibbāya sotadhātuyā "
"visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇātha dibbe ca mānuse ca ye dūre "
"santike cā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus do you, with clairaudience that is purified "
"and superhuman, hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or "
"far?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:6.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.122"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:7.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā parasattānaṃ "
"parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānātha—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ sarāgaṃ "
"cittanti pajānātha; vītarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ vītarāgaṃ cittanti pajānātha; "
"sadosaṃ vā cittaṃ sadosaṃ cittanti pajānātha; vītadosaṃ vā cittaṃ vītadosaṃ "
"cittanti pajānātha; samohaṃ vā cittaṃ samohaṃ cittanti pajānātha; vītamohaṃ "
"vā cittaṃ vītamohaṃ cittanti pajānātha; saṅkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ saṅkhittaṃ "
"cittanti pajānātha; vikkhittaṃ vā cittaṃ vikkhittaṃ cittanti pajānātha; "
"mahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ mahaggataṃ cittanti pajānātha; amahaggataṃ vā cittaṃ "
"amahaggataṃ cittanti pajānātha; sauttaraṃ vā cittaṃ sauttaraṃ cittanti "
"pajānātha; anuttaraṃ vā cittaṃ anuttaraṃ cittanti pajānātha; samāhitaṃ vā "
"cittaṃ samāhitaṃ cittanti pajānātha; asamāhitaṃ vā cittaṃ asamāhitaṃ "
"cittanti pajānātha; vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ cittanti pajānātha; "
"avimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ avimuttaṃ cittanti pajānāthā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you understand the minds of other beings "
"and individuals, having comprehended them with your mind? Do you understand "
"mind with greed as ‘mind with greed’, and mind without greed as ‘mind "
"without greed’? Do you understand mind with hate as ‘mind with hate’, and "
"mind without hate as ‘mind without hate’? Do you understand mind with "
"delusion as ‘mind with delusion’, and mind without delusion as ‘mind without "
"delusion’? Do you understand contracted mind as ‘contracted mind’, and "
"scattered mind as ‘scattered mind’? Do you understand expansive mind as ‘"
"expansive mind’, and unexpansive mind as ‘unexpansive mind’? Do you "
"understand mind that is not supreme as ‘mind that is not supreme’, and mind "
"that is supreme as ‘mind that is supreme’? Do you understand mind immersed "
"in samādhi as ‘mind immersed in samādhi’, and mind not immersed in samādhi "
"as ‘mind not immersed in samādhi’? Do you understand freed mind as ‘freed "
"mind’, and unfreed mind as ‘unfreed mind’?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:7.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:8.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā anekavihitaṃ "
"pubbenivāsaṃ anussaratha, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo tissopi "
"jātiyo catassopi jātiyo pañcapi jātiyo dasapi jātiyo vīsampi jātiyo tiṃsampi "
"jātiyo cattārīsampi jātiyo paññāsampi jātiyo jātisatampi jātisahassampi "
"jātisatasahassampi, anekepi saṃvaṭṭakappe anekepi vivaṭṭakappe anekepi "
"saṃvaṭṭavivaṭṭakappe: ‘amutrāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro "
"evaṃsukhadukkhapaṭisaṃvedī evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto amutra udapādiṃ; "
"tatrāpāsiṃ evaṃnāmo evaṅgotto evaṃvaṇṇo evamāhāro evaṃsukhadukkhapaṭisaṃvedī "
"evamāyupariyanto, so tato cuto idhūpapanno’ti. Iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarathā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you recollect many kinds of past lives. "
"That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a "
"hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world "
"contracting, many eons of the world evolving, many eons of the world "
"contracting and evolving? Do you remember: ‘There, I was named this, my clan "
"was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt "
"pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from "
"that place I was reborn somewhere else. There, too, I was named this, my "
"clan was that, I looked like this, and that was my food. This was how I felt "
"pleasure and pain, and that was how my life ended. When I passed away from "
"that place I was reborn here.’ Do you recollect your many kinds of past "
"lives, with features and details?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:8.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.123"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:9.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā dibbena cakkhunā "
"visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passatha cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne "
"paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānātha: ‘ime "
"vata bhonto sattā kāyaduccaritena samannāgatā vacīduccaritena samannāgatā "
"manoduccaritena samannāgatā, ariyānaṃ upavādakā micchādiṭṭhikā "
"micchādiṭṭhikammasamādānā, te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā apāyaṃ duggatiṃ "
"vinipātaṃ nirayaṃ upapannā; ime vā pana bhonto sattā kāyasucaritena "
"samannāgatā vacīsucaritena samannāgatā manosucaritena samannāgatā, ariyānaṃ "
"anupavādakā sammādiṭṭhikā sammādiṭṭhikammasamādānā te kāyassa bhedā paraṃ "
"maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapannā’ti, iti dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena "
"atikkantamānusakena satte passatha cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe "
"dubbaṇṇe, sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāthā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you, with clairvoyance that is purified "
"and superhuman, see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior "
"and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place—and "
"understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds? ‘These "
"dear beings did bad things by way of body, speech, and mind. They spoke ill "
"of the noble ones; they had wrong view; and they chose to act out of that "
"wrong view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a "
"place of loss, a bad place, the underworld, hell. These dear beings, "
"however, did good things by way of body, speech, and mind. They never spoke "
"ill of the noble ones; they had right view; and they chose to act out of "
"that right view. When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in a "
"good place, a heavenly realm.’ And so, with clairvoyance that is purified "
"and superhuman, do you see sentient beings passing away and being reborn—"
"inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. "
"And do you understand how sentient beings are reborn according to their "
"deeds?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:9.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:10.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tumhe āyasmanto evaṃ jānantā evaṃ passantā ye te santā vimokkhā "
"atikkamma rūpe āruppā, te kāyena phusitvā viharathā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you have direct meditative experience of "
"the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:10.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”."
msgstr "“No, reverend.”"

# See BB for readings.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:11.1"
msgid ""
"“Ettha dāni āyasmanto idañca veyyākaraṇaṃ imesañca dhammānaṃ asamāpatti; "
"idaṃ no, āvuso, kathan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well now, venerables, how could there be such a declaration when these "
"things are not attained?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:11.2"
msgid "“Paññāvimuttā kho mayaṃ, āvuso susimā”ti."
msgstr "“Reverend Susīma, we are freed by wisdom.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.124"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:12.1"
msgid ""
"“Na khvāhaṃ imassa āyasmantānaṃ saṅkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ "
"ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"“I don’t understand the detailed meaning of what you have said in brief."

msgctxt "sn12.70:12.2"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me āyasmanto tathā bhāsantu yathāhaṃ imassa āyasmantānaṃ saṅkhittena "
"bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājāneyyan”ti."
msgstr "Please teach me this matter so I can understand the detailed meaning.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:12.3"
msgid ""
"“Ājāneyyāsi vā tvaṃ, āvuso susima, na vā tvaṃ ājāneyyāsi atha kho "
"paññāvimuttā mayan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Susīma, whether you understand or not, we are freed by wisdom.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā susimo uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr "Then Susīma went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "sn12.70:13.2"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā susimo yāvatako tehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ ahosi "
"kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi."
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all he had discussed with those mendicants."

msgctxt "sn12.70:13.3"
msgid "“Pubbe kho, susima, dhammaṭṭhitiñāṇaṃ, pacchā nibbāne ñāṇan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“Susīma, first comes knowledge of the stability of natural principles. "
"Afterwards there is knowledge of extinguishment.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: bhagavatā → bhagavato (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.70:14.1"
msgid ""
"“Na khvāhaṃ, bhante, imassa bhagavatā saṃkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena "
"atthaṃ ājānāmi."
msgstr ""
"“Sir, I don’t understand the detailed meaning of what you have said in brief."

#. VAR: bhagavatā → bhagavato (pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn12.70:14.2"
msgid ""
"Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā tathā bhāsatu yathāhaṃ imassa bhagavatā "
"saṃkhittena bhāsitassa vitthārena atthaṃ ājāneyyan”ti."
msgstr "Please teach me this matter so I can understand the detailed meaning.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:14.3"
msgid ""
"“Ājāneyyāsi vā tvaṃ, susima, na vā tvaṃ ājāneyyāsi, atha kho "
"dhammaṭṭhitiñāṇaṃ pubbe, pacchā nibbāne ñāṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Susīma, whether you understand or not, first comes knowledge of "
"the stability of natural principles. Afterwards there is knowledge of "
"extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.125"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:15.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, susima, "
msgstr "What do you think, Susīma? "

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.6"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.9"
msgid "“Vedanā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is feeling permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.10"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.11"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.12"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.13"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.14"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.15"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.16"
msgid "“Saññā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is perception permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.17"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante” … pe …"
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.” …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.18"
msgid "“saṅkhārā niccā vā aniccā vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Are choices permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.19"
msgid "“Aniccā, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.20"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if they’re impermanent, are they suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.21"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.22"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if they’re impermanent, suffering, and perishable, are they fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.23"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.24"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.25"
msgid "“Viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.26"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.27"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.28"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.29"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and perishable, is it fit to be "
"regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.30"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:15.31"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:16.1"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha, susima, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā "
"bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, "
"sabbaṃ rūpaṃ netaṃ mama nesohamasmi na meso attāti; evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So, Susīma, you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or "
"present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or "
"near: <em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am "
"not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn12.70:16.2"
msgid ""
"Yā kāci vedanā atītānāgatapaccuppannā ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikā vā "
"sukhumā vā hīnā vā paṇītā vā yā dūre santike vā, sabbā vedanā netaṃ mama "
"nesohamasmi na meso attāti; evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"You should truly see any kind of feeling at all—past, future, or present; "
"internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: "
"<em>all</em> feeling—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not "
"this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn12.70:16.3"
msgid "Yā kāci saññā … pe …"
msgstr ""
"You should truly see any kind of perception at all—past, future, or present; "
"internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: "
"<em>all</em> perception—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am "
"not this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn12.70:16.4"
msgid ""
"ye keci saṅkhārā atītānāgatapaccuppannā ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikā vā "
"sukhumā vā hīnā vā paṇītā vā ye dūre santike vā, sabbe saṅkhārā netaṃ mama "
"nesohamasmi na meso attāti; evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"You should truly see any kind of choices at all—past, future, or present; "
"internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: <em>"
"all choices</em>—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, "
"this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn12.70:16.5"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ "
"vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ viññāṇaṃ "
"netaṃ mama nesohamasmi na meso attāti; evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ sammappaññāya "
"daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"You should truly see any kind of consciousness at all—past, future, or "
"present; internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or "
"near: <em>all</em> consciousness—with right understanding: ‘This is not "
"mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:17.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, susima, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi "
"nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, "
"feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn12.70:17.2"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati, virāgā vimuccati, vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn12.70:17.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.126"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:18.1"
msgid "‘Jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇan’ti, susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "Susīma, do you see that rebirth is a condition for old age and death?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.3"
msgid "“‘Bhavapaccayā jātī’ti, susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you see that continued existence is a condition for rebirth?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.5"
msgid "“‘Upādānapaccayā bhavo’ti, susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you see that grasping is a condition for continued existence?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.7"
msgid "“‘Taṇhāpaccayā upādānan’ti, susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you see that craving is a condition for grasping?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.8"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.9"
msgid "“Vedanāpaccayā taṇhāti …"
msgstr "“Do you see that feeling is a condition for craving …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.10"
msgid "phassapaccayā vedanāti …"
msgstr "contact is a condition for feeling …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.11"
msgid "saḷāyatanapaccayā phassoti …"
msgstr "the six sense fields are conditions for contact …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.12"
msgid "nāmarūpapaccayā saḷāyatananti …"
msgstr "name and form are conditions for the six sense fields …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.13"
msgid "viññāṇapaccayā nāmarūpanti …"
msgstr "consciousness is a condition for name and form …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.14"
msgid "saṅkhārapaccayā viññāṇanti …"
msgstr "choices are a condition for consciousness …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.15"
msgid "avijjāpaccayā saṅkhārāti, susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "ignorance is a condition for choices?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:18.16"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:19.1"
msgid "“‘Jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇanirodho’ti, susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you see that when rebirth ceases old age and death cease?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.2"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.3"
msgid "“‘Bhavanirodhā jātinirodho’ti susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Do you see that when continued existence ceases rebirth ceases?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.5"
msgid "“Upādānanirodhā bhavanirodhoti …"
msgstr "“Do you see that when grasping ceases continued existence ceases …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.6"
msgid "taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodhoti …"
msgstr "when craving ceases, grasping ceases …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.7"
msgid "vedanānirodhā taṇhānirodhoti …"
msgstr "when feeling ceases, craving ceases …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.8"
msgid "phassanirodhā vedanānirodhoti …"
msgstr "when contact ceases, feeling ceases …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.9"
msgid "saḷāyatananirodhā phassanirodhoti …"
msgstr "when the six sense fields cease, contact ceases …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.10"
msgid "nāmarūpanirodhā saḷāyatananirodhoti …"
msgstr "when name and form cease, the six sense fields cease …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.11"
msgid "viññāṇanirodhā nāmarūpanirodhoti …"
msgstr "when consciousness ceases name and form cease …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.12"
msgid "saṅkhāranirodhā viññāṇanirodhoti …"
msgstr "when choices cease consciousness ceases …"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.13"
msgid "avijjānirodhā saṅkhāranirodhoti, susima, passasī”ti?"
msgstr "when ignorance ceases choices cease?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:19.14"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:20.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tvaṃ, susima, evaṃ jānanto evaṃ passanto anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ "
"paccanubhosi—ekopi hutvā bahudhā hosi, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hosi; āvibhāvaṃ, "
"tirobhāvaṃ, tirokuṭṭaṃ tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchasi, "
"seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi ummujjanimujjaṃ karosi, seyyathāpi udake; "
"udakepi abhijjamāno gacchasi, seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena "
"kamasi, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike "
"evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimasasi parimajjasi, yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena "
"vasaṃ vattesī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But knowing and seeing thus, do you wield the many kinds of psychic power? "
"…”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:20.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.127"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:21.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tvaṃ, susima, evaṃ jānanto evaṃ passanto dibbāya sotadhātuyā "
"visuddhāya atikkantamānusikāya ubho sadde suṇasi dibbe ca mānuse ca ye dūre "
"santike cā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus do you, with clairaudience that is purified "
"and superhuman, hear both kinds of sounds, human and divine, whether near or "
"far?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:21.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc22"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:22.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tvaṃ, susima, evaṃ jānanto evaṃ passanto parasattānaṃ "
"parapuggalānaṃ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāsi—sarāgaṃ vā cittaṃ sarāgaṃ "
"cittanti pajānāsi … pe … vimuttaṃ vā cittaṃ vimuttaṃ cittanti pajānāsī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you understand the minds of other beings "
"and individuals, having comprehended them with your mind? …”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:22.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc23"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:23.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tvaṃ, susima, evaṃ jānanto evaṃ passanto anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ "
"anussarasi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ "
"anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you recollect many kinds of past lives, "
"with features and details?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:23.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc24"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:24.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tvaṃ, susima, evaṃ jānanto evaṃ passanto dibbena cakkhunā "
"visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passasi cavamāne … pe … yathākammūpage "
"satte pajānāsī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you, with clairvoyance that is purified "
"and superhuman, see sentient beings passing away and being reborn … "
"according to their deeds?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:24.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc25"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:25.1"
msgid ""
"“Api pana tvaṃ, susima, evaṃ jānanto evaṃ passanto ye te santā vimokkhā "
"atikkamma rūpe āruppā, te kāyena phusitvā viharasī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well, knowing and seeing thus, do you have direct meditative experience of "
"the peaceful liberations that are formless, transcending form?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:25.2"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc26"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:26.1"
msgid ""
"“Ettha dāni, susima, idañca veyyākaraṇaṃ imesañca dhammānaṃ asamāpatti, idaṃ "
"no, susima, kathan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Well now, Susīma, how could there be such a declaration when these things "
"are not attained?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc27"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:27.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā susimo bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Susīma bowed with his head at the Buddha’s feet and said:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:27.2"
msgid ""
"“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yvāhaṃ "
"evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye dhammatthenako pabbajito."
msgstr ""
"“I have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of me to "
"go forth as a thief in such a well-explained teaching and training."

msgctxt "sn12.70:27.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa me, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, sir, accept my mistake for what it is, so I will restrain myself in "
"future.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi2.128"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc28"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.70:28.1"
msgid ""
"“Taggha tvaṃ, susima, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, "
"yo tvaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye dhammatthenako pabbajito."
msgstr ""
"“Indeed, Susīma, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful "
"of you to go forth as a thief in such a well-explained teaching and training."

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, susima, coraṃ āgucāriṃ gahetvā rañño dasseyyuṃ:"
msgstr ""
"Suppose they were to arrest a bandit, a criminal and present him to the "
"king, saying:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.3"
msgid "‘ayaṃ te, deva, coro āgucārī, imassa yaṃ icchasi taṃ daṇḍaṃ paṇehī’ti."
msgstr "‘Your Majesty, this is a bandit, a criminal. Punish him as you will.’"

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.4"
msgid "Tamenaṃ rājā evaṃ vadeyya:"
msgstr "The king would say:"

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.5"
msgid ""
"‘gacchatha, bho, imaṃ purisaṃ daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ "
"bandhitvā khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathiyāya rathiyaṃ "
"siṅghāṭakena siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhāmetvā dakkhiṇato "
"nagarassa sīsaṃ chindathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Go, my men, and tie this man’s arms tightly behind his back with a strong "
"rope. Shave his head and march him from street to street and from square to "
"square to the beating of a harsh drum. Then take him out the south gate and "
"there, to the south of the city, chop off his head.’"

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.6"
msgid ""
"Tamenaṃ rañño purisā daḷhāya rajjuyā pacchābāhaṃ gāḷhabandhanaṃ bandhitvā "
"khuramuṇḍaṃ karitvā kharassarena paṇavena rathiyāya rathiyaṃ siṅghāṭakena "
"siṅghāṭakaṃ parinetvā dakkhiṇena dvārena nikkhāmetvā dakkhiṇato nagarassa "
"sīsaṃ chindeyyuṃ."
msgstr "The king’s men would do as they were told."

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.7"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, susima, "
msgstr "What do you think, Susīma? "

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.8"
msgid "api nu so puriso tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvediyethā”ti?"
msgstr "Wouldn’t that man experience pain and distress because of that?”"

msgctxt "sn12.70:28.9"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Yes, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc29"></a>
#. VAR: paṭisaṃvediyetha → paṭisaṃvedayetha (bj, s1-3) | patisaṃvediyetha vā na vā paṭisaṃvediyetha (pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn12.70:29.1"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ kho so, susima, puriso tatonidānaṃ dukkhaṃ domanassaṃ paṭisaṃvediyetha."
msgstr "“Although that man would experience pain and distress because of that,"

msgctxt "sn12.70:29.2"
msgid ""
"Yā evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye dhammatthenakassa pabbajjā, ayaṃ tato "
"dukkhavipākatarā ca kaṭukavipākatarā ca, api ca vinipātāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"going forth as a thief in such a well-explained teaching and training has a "
"more painful and bitter result. And it even leads to the underworld."

msgctxt "sn12.70:29.3"
msgid ""
"Yato ca kho tvaṃ, susima, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi taṃ "
"te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma."
msgstr ""
"But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt "
"with it properly, I accept it."

#. VAR: āyatiñca → āyatiṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn12.70:29.4"
msgid ""
"Vuddhi hesā, susima, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ "
"paṭikaroti, āyatiñca saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for "
"what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.70:29.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.70:29.6"
msgid "Mahāvaggo sattamo."
msgstr ""

